<div class="blog-faq">
<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>How long does a typical cosmetic surgery consultation last?</h3>
<p>A typical consultation lasts between 30 minutes to one hour, depending on the complexity of the procedures you are considering. This time allows for a thorough discussion of your goals, a physical examination, review of options, and an opportunity to ask all of your questions.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>What is the safest cosmetic surgery procedure?</h3>
<p>Non-surgical treatments like Botox and dermal fillers are generally considered among the safest options with the lowest risk profiles. Among surgical procedures, the safety depends largely on the patient's health, the surgeon's skill, and the facility's standards. All procedures at Dr. Johar's clinic are performed under strict safety protocols.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>How long after cosmetic surgery can I return to work?</h3>
<p>Return to work depends on the procedure and your job's physical demands. After minor procedures, you may return within 2 to 3 days. After more extensive surgeries like facelifts or abdominoplasty, most patients take 1 to 2 weeks off. Your surgeon will provide specific guidance based on your procedure.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>Are cosmetic surgery results permanent?</h3>
<p>Results vary by procedure. Surgical results like rhinoplasty and facelift are long-lasting but not necessarily permanent, as aging continues. Non-surgical treatments like Botox and fillers are temporary and require maintenance. Your surgeon will discuss the expected longevity of results for your specific procedure.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>What should I eat before cosmetic surgery?</h3>
<p>Your surgeon will provide specific pre-operative dietary instructions. Generally, patients are advised to eat a nutritious diet, stay well-hydrated, and avoid alcohol in the days leading up to surgery. You will typically need to fast for 6 to 8 hours before the procedure. Detailed guidance is available on the <a href="https://www.theaesthetic.in/post-op-instructions-plastic-reconstructive-surgeon-noida-up/">post-op care page</a>.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>Can I get cosmetic surgery if I have a medical condition?</h3>
<p>Many patients with controlled medical conditions can safely undergo cosmetic surgery. Conditions like diabetes, hypertension, and thyroid disorders must be well-managed. A thorough medical evaluation during your consultation helps determine your suitability for surgery. Always disclose your complete medical history to your surgeon.</p>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<h3>How do I schedule a consultation with Dr. Manoj K Johar?</h3>
<p>You can schedule a consultation by calling <strong>+91 85277 78462</strong> directly or by visiting the <a href="https://www.theaesthetic.in/general-appointment-plastic-reconstructive-surgeon-noida-up/">appointment page</a> on the website. The clinic team will assist you in finding a convenient time for your visit.</p>
</div>
</div>

